sentence: He went for more aspirin later in the day , and passed the surly landlord on the way -- he was still alive and scowling as usual , as if tenants were a burden in his life .
mut.sentence: He went for some more aspirin later in the day, and passed the surly landlord on the way -- he was still alive and scowling as usual, as if tenants were a significant burden in his life.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'tenants'的含义没有发生变化。在原句和变异句中，'tenants'都指的是房东的房客，且都被描述为房东生活中的负担。变异句中加入了'significant'这个词，但并没有改变'tenants'作为房客的含义，只是强调了他们是一个重要的负担，而不是改变了负担的性质。因此，目标词的含义没有差异。

sentence: I had to reach back to French 101 when the monsieur avec clipboard leaned over my shoulder during the coffee phase of dinner and asked whether I wanted to ride in a montgolfiere .
mut.sentence: I had to reach back to French one-oh-one when the monsieur avec clipboard leaned over my shoulder during the coffee phase of dinner and asked whether I wanted to ride in a montgolfiere.
reason: 原句和变异句中的目标词'reach'在这里的含义是一致的。'Reach back'在这里指的是回忆起或重新接触到过去学过的知识，即作者需要回想他在法语101课程中学到的内容来理解或回应'monsieur avec clipboard'的问题。在两个句子中，'reach'的使用情境和上下文含义没有变化，因此含义相同。

sentence: With membership of the Church of England steadily dwindling , strong-willed vicars are pressing equally strong-willed and often non-religious ringers to attend services .
mut.sentence: With the membership of the Church of England gradually declining, strong-willed vicars are urging a number of equally strong-willed and frequently non-religious ringers to attend services.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'membership'的含义是一致的。'membership'指的是教会成员的身份或者资格，在这里指的是英格兰教会的成员数量。原句和变异句都描述了英格兰教会成员数量逐渐减少的情况，没有表现出目标词在不同句子中有不同的含义。

sentence: Phil usually went alone and kept to himself , sitting in a corner and passing the time by nursing his favorite grudges .
mut.sentence: Phil usually went by himself and kept to a single corner, sitting there and passing the time by nursing his few favorite grudges.
reason: 在原句中，'corner'指的是一个抽象的空间概念，即Phil选择坐在一个相对隔离的位置，独自一人。而在变异句中，'corner'可能不仅仅指空间上的角落，还可能暗示Phil的行为模式也像被限制在一个角落里，单一不变。此外，变异句中的'a single corner'比原句的'in a corner'多了一层强调，似乎更加强调了Phil的孤立和不变的行为。因此，尽管两个句子中的'corner'都与空间位置有关，但变异句中的含义更为丰富，存在不同的侧重点。

sentence: The claim could force appeals judges to grapple with the question of whether new technology requires new courtroom rules .
mut.sentence: The claim could force several judges to grapple with the question of whether new technology requires new courtroom rules.
reason: 两个句子中的目标词 'rules' 在上下文中含义相同，都指的是法庭上需要遵守的规章制度。原句中的 'appeals judges' 和变异句中的 'several judges' 都面临同样的问题，即新技术是否需要新的法庭规则。因此，目标词 'rules' 的含义没有变化。

sentence: `` Only a decade ago cancer was a black box about which we knew nothing at the molecular level .
mut.sentence: Only a few years ago cancer was a black box about which we knew very little at the molecular level.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词 'knew' 的含义可以有所不同。在原句中，'knew nothing' 表示对癌症分子层面的知识完全无知，而在变异句中，'knew very little' 则表示对这一领域的了解有限但并非一无所知。因此，两个句子中的 'knew' 反映了不同程度的知识掌握，含义上有所区别。

sentence: Forged by a U.N. ad-hoc working group , the text is silent on how much money rich countries would give poor ones to cope with global warming over the short and long term .
mut.sentence: Forged by a U.N. ad-hoc working group, the text is silent on how much money wealthy countries would give to a number of poor ones to cope with global warming over the short and long term.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词 'ones' 都指代前文提到的 'countries'，并且含义相同。在原句中，'poor ones' 指的是贫穷的国家；在变异句中，'a number of poor ones' 也同样指代一系列贫穷的国家。尽管变异句中多了 'a number of' 这个短语，但 'ones' 的含义并没有改变，仍然是复数形式的可数名词，指代多个国家。因此，两个句子中 'ones' 的含义是一致的。

sentence: In interviews , some journalists said the claim that instant news was more incendiary than reports delivered more slowly was a Luddite view that would make poor court policy governing coverage of future trials .
mut.sentence: In interviews, several journalists claimed that the notion that instant news was more incendiary than reports delivered at a slower pace was a Luddite view that would make for poor court policy governing coverage of upcoming trials.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'policy'的含义是一致的。'policy'在这里指的是法院关于未来审判报道的指导方针或规则。原句中使用的是'make poor court policy'，而变异句中使用的是'make for poor court policy'，这两个短语在含义上是相似的，都表达了这种观点（即即时新闻比慢速报道更具煽动性）会导致制定出不好的法院政策。因此，目标词'policy'的含义没有发生变化。

sentence: The less complicated version of playing tunes on bells , as do the carillons of continental Europe , is considered by the English to be childish , fit only for foreigners .
mut.sentence: The simpler version of playing tunes on bells, as do many carillons in continental Europe, is considered by the English to be childish, fit only for foreigners.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'bells'的含义没有发生变化。'Bells'在原句和变异句中都指的是可以演奏旋律的钟，特别是指那些大陆欧洲的编钟（carillons）。无论是原句中的'less complicated version of playing tunes on bells'还是变异句中的'simpler version of playing tunes on bells'，都只是描述了演奏方式的复杂程度，而不是改变了'bells'本身的含义。因此，两个句子中的目标词含义相同。

sentence: Each legislator , after all , is only one out of 535 when it comes to national policy making .
mut.sentence: Each legislator, after all, is just one among hundreds when it comes to national policy making.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'policy'的含义没有发生变化。'policy'在两个句子中都指的是国家层面的政策制定过程或政策本身，而不是指不同的概念或范围。原句中的'535'和变异句中的'hundreds'都用来表达立法者在整个决策过程中的相对数量，但这并不影响'policy'这个词的含义。

sentence: 1 -RRB- Voters can `` buy `` one of two brands when they select their political agents -- a Republican brand that believes in the minimalist state and in the virtues of private markets over the vices of public action , and a Democratic brand that believes in big government and in public intervention to remedy the excesses attendant to the pursuit of private interest .
mut.sentence: Voters can `` buy `` one of a couple of brands when they select their political agents -- a Republican brand that believes in the minimalist state and in the virtues of private markets over the vices of public action , and a Democratic brand that believes in big government and in public intervention to remedy the excesses attendant to the pursuit of private interest .
reason: 原句和变异句中的目标词 'state' 在句子中的含义没有发生变化，都是指政治哲学中的国家或政府的状态或角色，即在这里指代政府的规模和干预程度。两个句子中的 'state' 都是指代共和党人所支持的 'minimalist state'（最小政府状态），其含义在两个句子中保持一致，没有体现出不同的含义。

sentence: Any question as to why an author would believe this plaintive , high-minded note of assurance is necessary is answered by reading this book about sticky fingers and sweaty scammers .
mut.sentence: Any question as to why an author would believe this plaintive , high-minded note of assurance is necessary is answered by reading a couple of chapters in this book about sticky fingers and sweaty scammers.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词 'answered' 的含义是相同的。'answered' 在这里指的是问题得到了解答或解释。原句和变异句中的区别仅在于阅读的范围（整本书还是几章），但这并不影响 'answered' 这个动词的含义。因此，两个句子中的目标词含义没有不同。

sentence: American companies walked away with stakes in just two of the 10 auctioned fields .
mut.sentence: American companies walked away with stakes in only a couple of the 10 auctioned fields.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'fields'的含义是一致的。'fields'在这里指的是被拍卖的领域或区块，通常指油气田或矿产开采区域。原句中的'two of the 10 auctioned fields'与变异句中的'only a couple of the 10 auctioned fields'表达的是相同的概念，即美国公司在十个被拍卖的区域中只获得了两个区域的股份。'couple'在此处是口语化的表达，相当于'two'，并不改变'fields'的含义。

sentence: I want to study your landlord 's habits and movements first .
mut.sentence: I want to study your landlord's habits and movements initially.

sentence: Dr. Vogelstein and a doctoral student , Eric Fearon , began months of tedious and often frustrating probing of the chromosomes searching for signs of genetic damage .
mut.sentence: Dr. Vogelstein and a doctoral student, Eric Fearon, began several months of tedious and often frustrating probing of the chromosomes searching for signs of genetic damage.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'months'的含义没有本质的区别。'Months'在原句中指的是一个持续了几个月的时间段，而在变异句中，'several months'也指的是一个持续了几个月的时间段，只是通过加入'several'稍微具体化了时间长度。但是，这并不改变'months'本身表示的时间范围的概念。因此，两个句子中的目标词含义相同。

sentence: We 've tried to train the youngsters , but they have their discos and their dances , and they just drift away . ``

sentence: Potential candidates may be discouraged from running less by the congressional salary than by the prospect of defeat at the hands of a Democratic opponent .
mut.sentence: Potential candidates may be discouraged from running not so much by the congressional salary as by the prospect of defeat at the hands of a single Democratic opponent.

sentence: Fears about the impact of immigrants are based on the notion that they are liable to replace native workers , in particular unskilled ones , exerting downward pressure on wages .
mut.sentence: Fears about the impact of immigrants are based on the notion that they are liable to replace a significant number of native workers, especially those who are unskilled, exerting downward pressure on wages.

sentence: Some researchers say new cancer drugs to slow or reverse tumor growth may be based on the suppressor proteins normally produced by the genes .
mut.sentence: Some researchers say several new cancer drugs to slow or reverse tumor growth may be based on the suppressor proteins normally produced by the genes.
reason: 原句和变异句中的目标词'reverse'在这里的含义是一致的。两个句子中的'reverse'都指的是阻止或逆转肿瘤生长的过程，没有因为在句子中的使用上下文不同而改变其基本含义。变异句只是增加了' several '这个词来修饰' new cancer drugs '，并不影响'reverse'这个词的含义。

sentence: Skilled ringers use their wrists to advance or retard the next swing , so that one bell can swap places with another in the following change .
mut.sentence: Skilled ringers use their wrists to advance or retard the subsequent swing, so that a single bell can swap places with another in the ensuing change.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'swing'的含义是一致的。'Swing'在这里指的是钟摆的运动或者钟铃的摆动。无论是原句中的'next swing'还是变异句中的'subsequent swing'，都描述了通过手腕的技术控制来调整下一个钟铃摆动的时机，以便在接下来的变化中与其他钟铃交换位置。'Next'和'subsequent'在这里是同义词，都表示接下来的意思，因此没有改变'swing'的基本含义。
